==English==

===Phrasal verb===
'''to [[keep]] [[up]]''' ('''keeping up''', '''kept up''', '''kept up''')

#To [[maintain]]; to [[preserve]]; to [[prevent]] from [[deteriorating]].
#To continue with (work, etc).
#to stay even or ahead
#:''They ran so fast I could hardly '''keep up'''.''

====Quotations====
(''maintain, preserve''):
*'''1992''' The NRA is pumping groundwater into the River Itchen in Hampshire to keep up its flow and is trying to save three streams, the Tong, the Little Stour and the Dour from going dry this summer. &mdash; ''The Daily Telegraph'', London: The Daily Telegraph plc
(''continue with''): 
*'''1991''' Keep up the good work of entertaining your fans on court Steffi; we know you can do it; your fans are behind you all the way. &mdash; ''Tennis World'', Sussex: Presswatch
*'''1991''' If the borrower could no longer afford to keep up the payments, the longer he stayed in the home the more the interest bill mounted.'' &mdash; ''The worst poverty, Barty-King, Hugh. Gloucester: Alan Sutton Publishing Ltd, 1991, pages 85-203

